ce:section.ce:para:
Through the Highway Fuel Economy Test (HWFET) and the Urban Dynamometer Driving Schedule (UDDS), the lithium batteries were subjected to a series of charge-discharge cycles. These tests can accurately measure key performance indicators such as capacity, cycle life, and power output of the lithium batteries. The experimental procedure included the following steps:


Step 1: Set the temperature of the thermostatic chamber to 25 °C;



Step 2: Allow the lithium battery to rest for 2 h before commencing experiments;



Step 3: Charge the battery at a constant current of 0.5C until the charge termination voltage of 4.2 V is reached, followed by constant voltage charging until the current drops below 0.05C, then stop charging;



Step 4: Let the battery rest for 2 h.



Step 5: Discharge the battery under HWFET and UDDS cycling conditions with a capacity limit of 253.01 mAh and a discharge termination voltage of 3.1 V.



Step 6: Let the battery rest for 2 h.



Step 7: Conclude the experiment.
